com.nimsoft.nimbus
Class PDS

java.lang.Object
  com.nimsoft.nimbus.PDS
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
Direct Known Subclasses:
OrderedPDS
public class PDS
extends Object
implements Serializable

Portable data format for Nimsoft Monitoring Solution.

Snippet 

 .....
 
      // Simple put / get int
 PDS pds = new PDS();
 
 int i = 1234567890;
 pds.put("key_i",i); // pds.putInt("key_i",i); // Does the same
      // And back again
 int j = pds.getInt("key_i");
      // Try a nonexisting key, this time with a default value
 j = pds.getInt("key_x",236);
 
 ....
 
      // Simple put / get Strings
 PDS pds = new PDS();
 
 pds.put("key_s","This is a test"); // pds.putString("key_s","This is a test"); // Does the same
 String s = pds.getString("key_s",null);  // Use default value null
 
 ....
 
      // PDS in PDS
 PDS pdshead = new PDS();
 PDS pds1 = new PDS();
 PDS pds2 = new PDS();
 
 pds2.put("double",(double)3.24);
 pds2.put("int",1234);
 pds1.put("pds2",pds2);
 pdshead.put("pds1",pds1);
 
 ....
 
      // Tables (arrays)
 PDS _pds = new PDS();
 
 int[] _is = new int[]{10,100,1000,10000,999999,1,2,3,4,5};
 
 pds.putTable("table_int",_is[0]);  // Put a single element in the table
 pds.putTable("table_int",_is[1]);
 pds.putTable("table_int",_is[2]);
 pds.putTable("table_int",_is[3]);
 pds.putTable("table_int",_is[4]);
 pds.putTable("table_int",new int[]{_is[5],_is[6],_is[7],_is[8],_is[9]}); // Put an additional array in the table
 
 int i = pds.getTableInt("table_int",8);  // Get only one specific element number 8 in the table (array)
 int[] is = pds.getTableInt("table_int"); // Get all the elements in the table (array)
Each send method causes the internal object measure values to be initialized to 0

getDecoding

public static String getDecoding()
Get the default character set used when Strings within PDS objects are created from byte arrays received on the bus. This charset will be used only if the PDS header does not specify a decoding character set and the charset has not been set for the session (use NimSessionBase.setCharset(String) and NimRequest.setCharset(String) to set a character set for a specific session).

Returns:
the default character set used to decode PDS objects.
